The paper deals with anomaly detection in dynamic networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networked systems (cs.NI). The methods proposed in the paper involve statistical modeling and large deviation theory, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the estimation of probability laws, which is a topic related to stochastic processes and information theory (cs.SI).
